name: Skunkling Font Family
description: Design Skunkling was designed for a competition put on by Design*Sponge and Veer, where it won 1st place. It was inspired by a real-life encounter between a spraying skunk and a defenseless designer. Skunkling is designed to give the impression of stylized hand-drawn lettering. 2 Font Variations The Inline font can be used alone as a one color font. Theline font can also be laid on top to add a secondary color, or used on its own as well.

name: Sullivan Font Family
description: Design Sullivan is the second typeface designed by Jason Mark Jones. Inspired by other bevel style fonts and hand drawn signage, it marries structure with personality. 3 Font Variations Use each font on its own or a combination of the fonts layered to create different beveled effects and shadows.
